I am trying to calculate the coverage in the bait regions for the lcWGS sequences.

So I need a bed file and bam files.
	Bams files are already made by the lcWGS pipeline
	Bed, however, the bed files of the baits doesn't have the same names for the nodes/chromosomes so this won't work (the baits were created using the SSL genome)

Thus,
  I need to make a bed file for the baits of Sfa using the published genome that was used in the Sfa lcWGS.
  For that I will have to map the baits in the published genome

Mapping
1.- get the bait sequences. 
cp /home/e1garcia/PIRE_ProbeTargets/19_Salarias_fasciatus/Baits_chosen.fas .

2. convert the fasta into fq.gz
	2.1 Split the baits sequences into r1 and r2 files (Sfa baits were made with 2 tile. tile 1 will be r1 and tile2 will be r2)
	less Baits_chosen.fas | paste - - | awk 'NR % 2 == 1' | tr '\t' '\n' > Sfa_chosen_baits-r1.fasta
        less Baits_chosen.fas | paste - - | awk 'NR % 2 == 0' | tr '\t' '\n' > Sfa_chosen_baits-r2.fasta

	2.2 Convert the fasta into fq files
	perl fasta_to_fastq.pl Sfa_chosen_baits-r1.fasta > Sfa_chosen_baits.R1.fq
	perl fasta_to_fastq.pl Sfa_chosen_baits-r2.fasta > Sfa_chosen_baits.R2.fq 
	
	2.3 compress fqs
	gzip Sfa_chosen_baits.R1.fq
	gzip Sfa_chosen_baits.R2.fq

3. Get genome ready
	copy genome used by mkBAM in lcWGS
	GCF_902148845.1_fSalaFa1.1_chr1-23-mtgen.fna.gz

	uncompress (not sure if dDocent likes compressed ref)
	gzip -d GCF_902148845.1_fSalaFa1.1_chr1-23-mtgen.fna.gz

	clean chromosome names
	sed -i -e 's/ Salarias fasciatus/_Sfa/' -e 's/ chromosome /_chr/' -e 's/ mitochondrion/_mtCompleteGenome/' -e 's/,.*//' GCF_902148845.1_fSalaFa1.1_chr1-23-mtgen.fna

	change name to dDocent ref scheme
	mv GCF_902148845.1_fSalaFa1.1_chr1-23-mtgen.fna reference.GCF_902148845.1_fSalaFa1_1_chr1-23-mtgen.fasta

4. Modify config to

----------mkREF: Settings for de novo assembly of the reference genome--------------------------------------------
PE              Type of reads for assembly (PE, SE, OL, RPE)                                    PE=ddRAD & ezRAD pairedend, non-overlapping reads; SE=singleend reads; OL=ddRAD & ezRA$
0.9             cdhit Clustering_Similarity_Pct (0-1)                                                   Use cdhit to cluster and collapse uniq reads by similarity threshold
GCF_902148845               Cutoff1 (integer)                                                                                         Use unique reads that have at least this much co$
1_fSalaFa1_1_chr1-23-mtgen               Cutoff2 (integer)
                Use unique reads that occur in at least this many individuals for making the reference genome
0.05    rainbow merge -r <percentile> (decimal 0-1)                                             Percentile-based minimum number of seqs to assemble in a precluster
0.95    rainbow merge -R <percentile> (decimal 0-1)                                             Percentile-based maximum number of seqs to assemble in a precluster
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I will try one with PE and one with RPE. not sure if this will matter.

5. Run
